result.execSummary:
The defendant Zeb C Ebel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: DC Jail request for sentence modification. Defendant requests a one day furlough. Court responds - you're scheduled for release next Wednesday, finish this condition time. DTE

Defendant Zeb C Ebel in court, in custody.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews events in file, reviews memo from DOC Agent Cassandra Downing. Deputy Schwartz indicates defendant has now provided a DNA sample.  Agent Downing indicates defendant continues to refuse to sign any releases.  Court questions whether refusal to sign those releases could result in revocation of his probation. Agent Downing not sure if defendant will be revoked or not, she'd have to discuss that issue with her supervisor. Defendant feels he has the right to refuse to sign those releases. Atty Pelrine makes statement. Defendant responds. Court makes statement to defendant, indicates to defendant he needs to sign those releases or face revocation of his probation. Defendant signs release form.
DC Jail Request for Sentence Modification - Defendant requests good time credit. Court denies request, responds - probation - condition time - no good time. DTE
from DOC agent Cassie Downing requesting a court review hearing. Court sets hearing.
Review hearing on August 8, 2016 at 01:15 pm.

DC Jail request for sentence modification - defendant requests furlough to visit his grandmother in the Dorchester. Court responds: one two hour furlough is okay with me but ultimately it's up to jail administration. There won't be "many" furloughs. DTE

Defendant Zeb C Ebel in court with attorney Eric R. Eickhoff.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minute sheet. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to Cts. 3 & 5. Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds pleas made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts pleas, and finds guilty of Cts. 3 & 5. Court dismisses Cts. 1, 2, 4, 6 & 7 but reads in for sentencing. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.

Atty Eickhoff asks court to amend cash bond to a signature bond or reduce cash bond to $250 to allow defendant to take care of some personal matters. State gives argument on bond. Atty Eickhoff responds. Court makes statement, not changing bond, remains at $1,500 cash.

Defendant Zeb C Ebel in court with attorney Eric R. Eickhoff.  Raymond Pelrine appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Copy of Complaint given to Defendant in Court.  Court reviews charge(s), max. penalties, right to counsel. Atty Eickhoff brings up issue of competency, feels defendant is ready to proceed today.  Defense waives reading of the complaint, enters not guilty plea. State requests a status in this case the same date as status in other pending matters.  Status conference scheduled for April 18, 2016 at 10:00 am.
No violent contact with W.E., S.E., G.E. Take any medications as prescribed. Not to the leave the State of Wisconsin.   To be fingerprinted and photographed before leaving the Justice Center.

Defendant Zeb C Ebel appears by video conference.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State gives incident report, potential charges. Court questions Defendant on address/employment history, reviews right to Counsel. Court finds probable cause, sets bond. Return 4/04/16 at 10:00 am.
